  Affiliations | Wilkins Investment Counsel, Inc.














Wilkins Investment Counsel, Inc.




Affiliations
Wilkins Investment Counsel is a member of the Investment Adviser Association, a national organization that represents the interests of SEC registered investment firms.
All members of the investment team belong to the Boston Security Analyst Society, Inc. , a community of investment professionals dedicated to promoting the highest ethical standards for the benefit of clients and the broad investing public.
In addition, all members of the investment team are members of the CFA Institute, a global community of investment professionals dedicated to shaping and upholding the highest educational and ethical standards serving investors and the wider public. Each investment team member has completed the CFA Program, a globally recognized, graduate-level curriculum that provides a strong foundation of real-world investment analysis and portfolio management skills, and has earned the Chartered Financial Analyst designation.
Certain members of the investment team are members of the Boston Economic Club, an organization of professionals engaged in the areas of economic and financial analysis, study or management and who hold leadership positions within the Boston business, governmental, financial, educational and legal communities.





























  Client Service | Wilkins Investment Counsel, Inc.














Wilkins Investment Counsel, Inc.




Client Service
At Wilkins Investment Counsel, Inc., we take pride in our strong service culture. We value every one of our clients and enjoy trusted, long lasting relationships with each, some of which span both decades and generations.
Your account is managed by a senior investment professional and all individual securities are under the continuous supervision of our dedicated research team.
Communication is critical and we stress frequent interaction with clients. This is accomplished via letters on a quarterly basis containing a portfolio appraisal and analysis, as well as our Quarterly Investment Outlook which provides a broad overview of our current thinking on the economy and the markets.
We recommend at least one in-depth meeting per year with every client and ongoing informal communication is strongly encouraged to keep us abreast of clients’ needs.





























  Team | Wilkins Investment Counsel, Inc.














Wilkins Investment Counsel, Inc.




Team


 
John P. Wilkins,CFA, CICShareholder, Chairman
John is a graduate of Colgate University (magna cum laude) and the University of Chicago Law School. He began his investment career in New York City as a research analyst for H.C. Wainwright & Co. and later became an investment officer for Citibank. Returning to his native Boston, John joined Standish, Ayer & Wood, Inc., as a Partner and Managing Director.
John has served as Board Chairman and President of the Investment Adviser Association, a national organization that represents the interests of SEC registered investment firms. He also serves as a Trustee (formerly Board Chairman) of YMCA Camp Belknap, and as Honorary Trustee of the New England Baptist Hospital, having previously been Board Chairman. He is a Director of Care Group, Inc., a holding company for Beth Israel Deaconess, Mt. Auburn and New England Baptist hospitals. John is also on the investment committee of the Carleton-Willard Village, Inc. retirement community. In his home community, John is the Endowment Chair of the Eliot Church and was a founding trustee of the Wellesley Free Library Centennial Fund.
John holds designations as a Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) and a Chartered Investment Counselor (CIC). He is a member of the Boston Economic Club.



 
Michael F. Charland,CFA, CIC Shareholder, President
Mike graduated from Bates College where he majored in economics and mathematics. He earned an MBA degree (cum laude) from Babson College. At Wilkins Investment Counsel, Inc. Mike focuses on portfolio management, equity research, and oversees the operation of the firm. Prior to joining Wilkins he worked in fixed income trading and management at Eaton Vance in Boston.
Michael is very involved with his undergraduate alma mater, having served as Chairman of the Boston Bates Business Network. He holds the Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) and Chartered Investment Counselor (CIC) designations and is a member of the CFA Society Boston and the Boston Economic Club.



 
Shane M. Garman,CFA, CICShareholder, Vice President
Shane is a graduate of Indiana University where he majored in kinesiology. He earned an MBA degree (summa cum laude) from Babson College and managed a portion of the school’s endowment as a member of the Babson College Fund. As a Portfolio Manager & Director of Research at Wilkins, Shane manages client accounts/relationships and leads the equity/fixed income analyst team responsible for investment research. He is also the firm’s Treasurer and Chief Compliance Officer.
His previous experience includes working in product marketing at XOS Technology, Inc., holding assistant coaching positions with several NCAA basketball programs, and assisting the coaching staff of the NBA’s Cleveland Cavaliers. He holds the Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) and Chartered Investment Counselor (CIC) designations and is a member of the CFA Society Boston.



 
Thomas S. Terraccino,CFASenior Investment Analyst
Tom is a graduate of Carnegie Mellon University where he received a bachelor of science degree in business administration with a concentration in finance. Tom specializes in equity research at Wilkins with a particular emphasis in the technology sector. His previous experience includes equity research at Boston American Asset Management and Prudential Equity Group. He holds the Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) designation and is a member of the CFA Society Boston.



 
Peter W. Smith,CFASenior Investment Analyst 
Peter is a graduate of Bowdoin College where he majored in economics and was a four year member of the men’s varsity ice hockey team. He specializes in fixed income management and research at Wilkins. He previously served as a fixed income trader with Bank of New York Mellon. Peter holds the Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) designation and is a member of the CFA Society Boston.



 
David R. MacDougall,CFASenior Investment Analyst
David is a graduate of Northeastern University where he majored in finance and marketing. He earned an MBA degree from Boston College, graduating with honors. David specializes in equity research at Wilkins. His previous experience includes equity research and portfolio management at Boston Financial Management, Emerson Investment Management, and Crestwood Advisors. He holds the Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) designation and is a member of the CFA Society Boston.



 
David P. GatelyDirector of Operations
Dave is a graduate of Saint Anselm College where he majored in history. His previous experience includes serving as operations manager at Contravisory Investment Management and as an investment associate at Congress Asset Management.



 
Sarah R. ValerioOperations Administrator
Sarah graduated from the University of Mary Washington where she earned a Bachelor of Science in Business Administration. Her experience prior to joining Wilkins includes working at The Colony Group as a senior portfolio administrator and at State Street Bank in fund accounting.



 
Lucinda RyanAdministrative/Operations Associate 
Cindy earned her diploma in an accelerated program at Chandler School for Women. She has extensive experience as an administrative assistant, most recently as the Office Administrator at Environmental Resources Management, Inc.























