Company Overview of Wilkins Investment Counsel, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Wilkins Investment Counsel, Inc. is an employee owned investment manager. The firm primarily provides its services to high net worth individuals. It also manages accounts for families, charitable organizations, foundations, endowments, and corporations. The firm manages separate client-focused balanced portfolios for its clients. It invests in public equity and fixed income markets of the United States. The firm primarily invests in growth stocks across all market capitalizations. For its fixed income investments, the firm invests in short to intermediate term, high grade securities including U.S. government bonds, corporate bonds, and municipal bonds. It employs fundamental analysis to make...
Wilkins Investment Counsel, Inc. is an employee owned investment manager. The firm primarily provides its services to high net worth individuals. It also manages accounts for families, charitable organizations, foundations, endowments, and corporations. The firm manages separate client-focused balanced portfolios for its clients. It invests in public equity and fixed income markets of the United States. The firm primarily invests in growth stocks across all market capitalizations. For its fixed income investments, the firm invests in short to intermediate term, high grade securities including U.S. government bonds, corporate bonds, and municipal bonds. It employs fundamental analysis to make its investments. The firm conducts in-house research to make investment decisions. Wilkins Investment Counsel, Inc. was founded in 1989 and is based in Boston, Massachusetts.
