9




Industries


Investment Services & Portfolio Management




Company Description


Wilkins Investment Counsel (WIC) creates balanced portfolios that consist of high quality common stocks and short to intermediate term, highly rated fixed-income securities. They use asset allocation to determine the appropriate combination of investments to meet each client's needs for growth of principal and current income.Their equity strategy is a long-term strategy that seeks to identify growth stocks with distinct competencies. They employ proprietary fundamental research that focuses on company fundamentals and financials, industry attractiveness and the strength and experience of the company's management team and the board of directors. They select growth companies with better risk/return characteristics than those of the market as a whole and place emphasis on price and valuation. WIC evaluates a stock's performance by enhancement of company fundamentals rather than short-term price fluctuations. The firm tends to invest in the stocks of US large-cap companies in the consumer non-durables, health technology and process industries sectors. WIC maintains a very low turnover rate.WIC's fixed-income investment approach is based on a buy and hold strategy that focuses on short- to intermediate-term laddered portfolios. They invest in issues with of high credit quality in the US government, corporate and municipal sectors. The firm employs fundamental research to identify attractive yield spreads and investment opportunities. They also give attention to individual tax situations to maximize after-tax returns.




